Minnewaska Area Schools welcomes the new administration team for the 2020-21 school year!

💙💚💙 Join us in a Laker Pride celebration! 💙💚💙

Pictured L to R: Scott Lempka, E-3 Elementary School Principal; Sarah Suchy, 4-8 Middle School Principal; Rick Ellingworth, Interim Superintendent; and Nate Meissner, 9-12 High School Principal.

"They are talented, energetic, personable, and fun to be around. I can’t wait for our students and families to get to know them,” says Ellingworth.

To view the full press release, visit our website at https://www.minnewaska.k12.mn.us/school-news/new-administration-team/

post_text:
We are excited to tune in to the 2 p.m. press conference by MN Governor Walz. He will provide guidelines for the upcoming school year, and we have done extensive planning and strategizing around education models to best fit his potential recommendations and to remain flexible for our families throughout the school year.

After his announcement, we will meet as a team and communicate the MAS plan to all our district families by Tuesday, August 4th and reopening plan by Tuesday, August 11. The safety of our students, providing high-quality education, working with our families, and communication of ongoing updates are our highest priorities.

Minnewaska Community Members are encouraged to view or listen to tonight's commencement exercises as we recognize and honor the Minnewaska Area High School 2020 graduates. You can view it live on Minnewaska's own YouTube channel (go to YouTube and put in Minnewaska Lakers Live) or listen to Smooth Magic 107.1.

Commencement exercises are scheduled to begin at 8:00 PM this evening. Also, a reminder to cheer on our graduates as we celebrate a "Senior Salute" with our graduates parading through both Glenwood and Starbuck to allow our community to share in this celebration. Graduates will be driving through Glenwood between 5:05-5:15 followed by Starbuck between 5:20-5:30.

post_text: Please consider nominating a teacher!
shared_text:
MINNEWASKAPTA.WEEBLY.COM
Minnewaska PTA online Membership form

Minnewaska PTO
April 26 at 5:13 PM ·

2020 PTO Minnewaska Teacher of Excellence Awards

The Teacher of Excellence awards will be chosen from nominations by parents with children in the Minnewaska School District and /or students in the Minnewaska School District.

A Teacher of Excellence can have many different meanings. We would like you to explain how your nominees impacted your child and their growth.

The form may be used to nominate a teacher Pre-K through 12th grade in the Minnewaska School District. The form will be located in the Elementary Newsletter sent out by Mrs. Suchy or you can print out a copy and email or mail to Bobbi Jo Matt that is located on our website at https://minnewaskapta.weebly.com/

Please have nominations turned in by Friday, May 15th.
This year we are going to be able to recognize teachers in the following categories:
Elementary (PreK – 3rd)
Intermediate (4th - 6th)
Highschool (7th - 12th)
W.I.N Academy.

post_text:
Dear Minnewaska Class of 2020,

We haven't forgotten you! In fact, we think about you each and every day! Continue to work hard to become LAKER GRADUATES! We will work hard to reschedule events you are losing your senior year.

We will have a graduation ceremony! That's a promise, it might not be on the exact date and it may look slightly different; but you will be recognized as a graduate of Minnewaska Area Schools!

In closing, I've ordered 100 of these signs for you to display in the month of May in preparation for your big day! Everyone here at MAS will continue to work hard to create opportunities for memories just as soon as possible!

Chip Rankin
Superintendent
text:
Dear Minnewaska Class of 2020,

We haven't forgotten you! In fact, we think about you each and every day! Continue to work hard to become LAKER GRADUATES! We will work hard to reschedule events you are losing your senior year.

We will have a graduation ceremony! That's a promise, it might not be on the exact date and it may look slightly different; but you will be recognized as a graduate of Minnewaska Area Schools!

In closing, I've ordered 100 of these signs for you to display in the month of May in preparation for your big day! Everyone here at MAS will continue to work hard to create opportunities for memories just as soon as possible!

Chip Rankin
Superintendent

Minnewaska Area Community Education, Recreation & Activities
April 3 at 11:51 AM ·

Following the lead of many schools throughout the State of Minnesota and across the country, Minnewaska Area Schools will be turning on our lights at Marthaler Field and Veterans Field at Glenwood State Bank Stadium every Monday evening beginning April 6th as a beacon of hope for our students, staff, and community members! The lights will be on from 8:15 p.m. to 8:45 p.m. and be adjusted as daylight hours increase! GO LAKERS! We miss you!!

post_text:
Minnewaska Area Schools might be closed to students, but I couldn't be more proud of the work the staff continues to perform!

Over 200 meals alone were provided/delivered yesterday along, common sense distance learning plans are getting the final touches, and over 35 kids a day are receiving care so their parent can perform their essential duties!

I don't know of a better way to demonstrate LAKER PRIDE!!

Chip Rankin
Superintendent

post_text:
Attention Laker parents! Check out this video featuring our students, Mr. Lence, and Britt Rose promoting Operation Laker Pride at the high school.

We have incentivized our challenge and have assigned two to three teachers to each grade level. Whichever grade collects the most of their designated item puts their assigned teachers under the ice water bucket! AND, if each grade collects over 500 items, ALL of the assigned teachers will get doused!
Who will it be!?! Deadline for items is Friday at the end of the day! Go Lakers!
